      "reportFinalResult": "DONE",
      "reportRole": "implementer",
      "reportSummary": "Fixed the Knowledge latest-state query semantics in Phase 1.5A Query Layer. The core bug was that `minConfidence` was passed to `knowledgeStore.query()` before the \"pick latest per (entityId, factId)\" logic, causing newer sealed records (confidence=0) to be pre-filtered out at the SQL level and older correct-confidence records to be incorrectly returned as the current state. The fix moves all visibility filtering (includeSealed + minConfidence) to a single post-selection filter in `findKnowledge`, applied after the latest record has been determined. Added 3 new integration tests covering: (1) minConfidence with newer seal, (2) seal-then-restore rowid arbitration, (3) includeHistory + includeSealed.",
